text: Even if Michael's character has been recast I still won't find the character genuine as Scott Speedman is Michael Corvin end of. If Speedman wanted out fine, but recasting him when Speedman's portrail of him was so vital to Selene's story is a tough one to take. What is up with their daughter Eve not being in this? that's what's really confusing to me. I thought India Eisley was a powerful addition to the cast. Her performance of Eve was fascinating and touching in the sense of how it and added a whole new level of depth to Selene's character as a mother who now must protect her child at all costs. Looking back on how 'Awakening' ended it was heavily implied they were as mother and daughter in this fight to the end. Looks to me like that's not the case now which is a serious shame, that storyline had so much potential. Why introduce her at all if you're not going to utilise her character in future films? Eve being the first and only Tri - Blood Hybrid of her kind and the last living descendant Alexander Corvinus should be one of the key factors in this film (in my opinion anyway). As Selene said in 'Underworld Awakening' - "She's the key to winning this war." so use her!

text: Darn it....DARN IT!  AGAIN, they seem to be doing the same nonsense they did in the last movie!   The werewolves just look like generic villains that, for some reason, seem to have no likeable or relatable characters to root for or attach to and seem to have no female members..which makes ZERO sense.  They might as well call this "Underworld: Awakening 2." It's like the producers forgot the history of the franchise and forgot making Rise of the Lycans.  It was the vampires that had enslaved werewolves to work for them and protect them.  It was a vampire leader that took the first new type of werewolf (Lycan) away from his mother, while he was still a baby..right after shooting the mother, to raise and use him to make more Lycans.  It is that same vampire leader that started the war by murdering his own pregnant daughter..who had a love connection with the Lycan leader.  And then to make it worse..that vampire leader killed Selene's family and blamed it on Lycans..causing her to hate Lycans and spend years fighting them.  Werewolves defeated the vampires and won their freedom but were hunted down for centuries as the war waged on.  Now they want to make werewolves Nazi-like creatures that seem to only want destruction and make the blood-sucking slave drivers the victims/heroes??  Give us a break!  I mean I know that the main character is a vampire..and was banging the director..but come on!

text: I am sorry, but they are doing the same damn thing that has ruined any hope for the Resident Evil series. To continue a series past its prime is to run the risk of what we just saw. Once again, its a single female protagonist running a one man war against a disease infested being of near ultimate power for the sake of all. Sound familiar? Had a ton of love for the first 2 films, but past that, its a matter of a dev team not knowing when to say to hell with the all mighty dolla dolla and just simply keeping a series pure and solid in its initial execution. But instead we are met with sequel after sequel of drek not worth nearly the same dime of what came before. Alwhile, like all the shit beforehand, it will make a pretty penny. But to consider the Underworld series as a worthwhile bank from her on out is a mistake. And make no mistake, there will be at least 2 more shitshows later down the road. Gotta keep up with the equally pisspoor competition. And yeah, you are welcome to argue me. But just know, you are part of the hollywood shitfest problem that we are met with.
